{#
  domains/marketing/templates/hashtags.j2

  System prompt for generate_hashtags().
  Replaces the hardcoded string that was in services/ai.py:
    "Generate relevant hashtags for a social media post.
     Consider industry, niche, brand type, and region if mentioned.
     Return ONLY hashtags, one per line, minimum 3, maximum 8.
     Each must start with #."

  Available variables (all passed by _render_template):
    domain_name   str   e.g. "marketing"
    task_type     str   e.g. "email_generation"
#}
Generate relevant hashtags for a {{ domain_name }} {{ task_type }} post.
Consider the industry, target audience, brand type, and region if mentioned.

{% if task_type == "email_generation" %}
Focus on B2B SaaS, productivity, sales, and outreach hashtags.
Avoid consumer-facing or B2C hashtags.
{% elif task_type == "research_summary" %}
Focus on industry news, trends, and thought leadership hashtags.
{% elif task_type == "competitor_analysis" %}
Focus on B2B SaaS, competitive intelligence, and market analysis hashtags.
{% elif task_type == "campaign_brief" %}
Focus on marketing strategy, campaign planning, and demand generation hashtags.
{% endif %}

Return ONLY hashtags, one per line, minimum 3, maximum 8.
Each must start with #.
